The paper deals with string matching on graphs, which is a problem in graph algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also uses techniques from computational complexity theory, specifically the Orthogonal Vectors Hypothesis (OVH), which suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem of indexing graphs for efficient string matching is also related to the study of graph compression and succinct data structures, which fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the paper's use of self-reducibility techniques and lower bounds suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of theoretical computer science (cs.LG).
